2
1 permitted in an unusual situation involving a boiler of special
2 design or construction if the board is satisfied that a proposed
3 facility will provide a degree of safety commensurate with the
4 intent of this article.
5 (3) The department shall allow a class 5B boiler installer or
6 a class IV boiler repairer to complete periodic maintenance and
7 testing of controls and safety devices of a boiler system.
8 (4) (3) If the department receives an application and the
9 appropriate fee, the board may without examination register an
10 applicant for the use of a title described in section 931 if the
11 applicant is a boiler operator or stationary engineer who is
12 licensed or registered as a boiler operator or stationary engineer
13 in another state or country or in a municipality whose requirements
14 for licensure or registration are, at a minimum, substantially
15 equivalent to the requirements of this state for registration, as
16 determined by the board, and that other state or country or that
17 municipality extends the same privileges through reciprocity to a
18 boiler operator or stationary engineer who is registered in this
19 state.
20 (5) As used in this section:
21 (a) "Class 5B boiler installer" means an individual who has a
22 class 5B installer's license as described in R 339.5174 of the
23 Michigan Administrative Code.
24 (b) "Class IV boiler repairer" means an individual who has a
25 class IV license as described in R 339.5175 of the Michigan
26 Administrative Code.
